bob beamon biography at thehistorymakers.com   1968 summer olympics thumb|left|bob beamon in 1968 beamon entered the 1968 summer olympics in mexico city as the favorite , having won 22 of the 23 meets he had competed in that year , including a career best of 8.33 m ( equivalent to 27 ft . 4 in . ) and a world 's best of 8.39 m ( 27 ft . 6 1/2 in . )

20th century sports : bob beamon made his record 29 ' 2 1/2 " long jump in the thin air of this city in 1968

mexico city